History: History: M on immunosuppressant recently in hospital with cough, PNA.
Findings: Mild left base atelectasis/scarring is seen. No definite focal consolidation is seen. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. There may be mild pulmonary vascular congestion. Impression: Possible mild vascular congestion. No definite focal consolidation.
